24 Middagh Street, at the S.E. corner of Willow Street. This place was used as a Chop-house in 1815. Still standing in (1929).

1922.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

Willow Street, east side, at, adjoining and south of Middagh Street. Also seen are Nos. 24-26 Middagh Street, at and adjoining the S.E. corner of Willow Street. This corner building (No. 24), was a chop house in 1815. In 1836 it was the residence of Oliver Hutchinson. In 1922 a Mrs. Griswald owned it.

April 1922.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

24-32 Middagh Street, south side, between Willow and Hicks Streets. The corner house was a chop house in 1815. It became a residence in 1836.

April 1925.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
